The paper proposes a subspace clustering algorithm that addresses limitations in finding clusters in non-disjoint subspaces and scaling to large data, which are common challenges in data management (cs.DB) and data mining (cs.DM). The algorithm uses frequent pattern mining (cs.LG) and bottom-up clustering (cs.IR) strategies. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in bioinformatics and the Internet of Things, which are areas of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
